- Keep going straight.

19:11.818 --> 19:14.487
- Yeah!
<i>- That mojo that we've had</i>

19:14.529 --> 19:17.115
in the past was still there,
and it felt really good.

19:17.157 --> 19:18.783
Clean!

19:18.825 --> 19:21.119
<i>- Chris and the team's</i>
<i>impressive round robin</i>

19:21.161 --> 19:24.456
<i>earned them the spot</i>
<i>they needed in the quarters</i>

19:24.497 --> 19:26.916
<i>and looked to be</i>
<i>just the start</i>

19:26.958 --> 19:30.628
<i>of another frozen slide</i>
<i>to glory.</i>

19:30.670 --> 19:32.297
<i>- We were ready to play</i>
<i>anybody--</i>

19:32.339 --> 19:33.673
<i>didn't matter who came up.</i>

19:33.715 --> 19:35.550
<i>We all really felt like</i>
<i>we had a chance</i>

19:35.592 --> 19:38.053
to win that tournament.

19:40.138 --> 19:43.266
<i>- It was all setting up</i>
<i>perfectly...</i>

19:43.308 --> 19:45.393
<i>that is, until it wasn't.</i>

19:47.771 --> 19:50.398
<i>I got a knock on my door.</i>

19:50.440 --> 19:53.109
<i>There was just a lady</i>
<i>standing there.</i>

19:53.151 --> 19:55.695
<i>Just basically told me</i>
<i>that I had tested positive</i>

19:55.737 --> 19:59.616
for COVID the day prior
and that my tournament was over

19:59.657 --> 20:02.202
and I was gonna be
quarantined in Canada, um...

20:02.243 --> 20:04.412
for like the next ten days.

20:04.454 --> 20:06.706
Uh, wow, okay.
Sounds good.

20:12.587 --> 20:14.255
- I mean,
the World Championships

20:14.297 --> 20:15.674
was crazy this year.

20:22.097 --> 20:24.724
<i>The fact that positive tests</i>
<i>happened at the World,</i>

20:24.766 --> 20:27.102
<i>and one of them was our team</i>

20:27.143 --> 20:29.938
and it happened to be Chris,
uh, yeah.

20:29.979 --> 20:32.315
Little ironic.

20:32.357 --> 20:34.567
<i>- One of our coaches</i>
<i>is pounding on the door,</i>

20:34.609 --> 20:36.736
<i>and the last thing</i>
<i>we should be doing</i>

20:36.778 --> 20:38.405
is all congregating
in the hallway,

20:38.446 --> 20:39.906
but we're all just
freaking out.

20:39.948 --> 20:42.367
- And my coach calls me
individually.

20:42.409 --> 20:44.703
He's like,
"Hey, just so you know,

20:44.744 --> 20:47.622
like you need to be ready
to play third tomorrow."

20:47.664 --> 20:50.583
Okay. Like, I've always wanted
to try my hand at third,

20:50.625 --> 20:52.335
but maybe not at
the quarterfinals

20:52.377 --> 20:54.045
of the World Championships.

20:54.087 --> 20:56.172
- It was like a--
definitely a dark...

20:56.214 --> 20:58.675
put me--like mentally,
was in a dark spot

20:58.717 --> 21:01.553
that...that day
and that night.

21:06.516 --> 21:08.560
<i>I just figured</i>
<i>I was screwed</i>

21:08.601 --> 21:12.439
<i>and wasn't gonna get a chance</i>
<i>to play with the guys, and...</i>

21:12.480 --> 21:15.942
it was 45 minutes
before the game

21:15.984 --> 21:18.695
that I got a call from Phill
that was like, yo,

21:18.737 --> 21:19.988
you're gonna play, get ready.

21:21.531 --> 21:23.783
<i>- After a whirlwind</i>
<i>36 hours,</i>

21:23.825 --> 21:26.619
<i>Chris's test had been</i>
<i>deemed a false positive.</i>

21:26.661 --> 21:29.080
<i>He was eligible to play again,</i>

21:29.122 --> 21:31.791
<i>and the team wanted him</i>
<i>back on the ice...</i>

21:31.833 --> 21:34.210
<i>though there was</i>
<i>a slight catch.</i>

21:35.420 --> 21:37.130
<i>You can play with masks on,</i>

21:37.172 --> 21:38.506
<i>but that's the only way</i>
<i>we'll let you play.</i>

21:38.548 --> 21:40.133
We'll let Chris play,

21:40.175 --> 21:41.593
is if you go out
and play with masks.

21:41.634 --> 21:43.720
So we were like, yeah.

21:43.762 --> 21:45.847
Our best chance to win
is with Chris playing,

21:45.889 --> 21:48.308
'cause as much fun
as it would've been

21:48.350 --> 21:52.312
to try and play third,
I didn't really want to.

21:52.979 --> 21:55.106
<i>- Looks like</i>
<i>we're ready to go.</i>

21:55.148 --> 21:56.900
<i>- Trying to get ready</i>
<i>to play</i>

21:56.941 --> 21:59.527
<i>a world play-off game,</i>
<i>like in 45 minutes, was...</i>

21:59.569 --> 22:02.113
it was difficult but,
you know,

22:02.155 --> 22:04.741
the guys were there
and we gave 'em...

22:04.783 --> 22:06.951
we gave 'em
a really good fight.

22:06.993 --> 22:08.953
<i>- Great shot.</i>

22:08.995 --> 22:11.331
<i>USA will lead one nothing</i>

22:11.373 --> 22:13.833
<i>here after two ends.</i>

22:13.875 --> 22:15.752
<i>How mentally strong are we</i>

22:15.794 --> 22:17.837
<i>that we were able to, like,</i>
<i>go through this</i>

22:17.879 --> 22:20.382
emotional roller coaster
and then come out

22:20.423 --> 22:23.218
and put on an A-game against
another really great team.

22:25.887 --> 22:27.347
<i>- Couldn't walk it down</i>
<i>better than that.</i>

22:27.389 --> 22:30.141
<i>- Two wonderful shots</i>
<i>from Chris Plys.</i>

22:30.183 --> 22:31.976
- Chris was the best player
on the ice

22:32.018 --> 22:33.853
between either team
during that game.

22:33.895 --> 22:36.022
<i>- Yeah, he played</i>
<i>out of his mind,</i>

22:36.064 --> 22:37.774
<i>considering that situation,</i>

22:37.816 --> 22:40.068
and I think we all did.

22:41.611 --> 22:42.654
<i>- Very nice.</i>
- Good, John!

22:42.696 --> 22:44.531
<i>- That is a hard-fought 2</i>

22:44.572 --> 22:46.533
<i>for Team USA.</i>

22:46.574 --> 22:48.827
<i>U.S./Switzerland unfolded</i>

22:48.868 --> 22:51.162
<i>as an epic back and forth,</i>

22:51.204 --> 22:53.998
<i>and the match</i>
<i>hung in the balance</i>

22:54.040 --> 22:56.126
<i>as Shuster lined up</i>
<i>his final shot.</i>

22:56.167 --> 22:57.877
<i>- Final stone here</i>
<i>in end number ten</i>

22:57.919 --> 22:59.879
<i>for the Olympic champion.</i>

