24:59.499 --> 25:01.167
<i>around each other, and...</i>

25:01.209 --> 25:03.044
<i>I think it really just</i>
<i>prepared us to be</i>

25:03.086 --> 25:05.797
<i>as great of friends</i>
<i>as we've become now.</i>

25:05.839 --> 25:08.133
We're now enjoying
experiencing new things,

25:08.174 --> 25:09.884
you know,
together all the time.

25:09.926 --> 25:11.302
Oh, my gosh.

25:11.344 --> 25:13.680
<i>- And the next experience</i>
<i>that awaits--</i>

25:13.722 --> 25:15.557
<i>in November, in Omaha,</i>

25:15.598 --> 25:18.018
<i>is the Olympic trials,</i>

25:18.059 --> 25:20.020
<i>for which the most</i>
<i>important prep</i>

25:20.061 --> 25:22.147
<i>comes on frozen ground.</i>

25:30.030 --> 25:31.322
- Steiner, you animal!
- Curl!

25:33.491 --> 25:35.869
<i>Team Shuster 2.0</i>

25:35.910 --> 25:38.079
<i>may be a work in progress,</i>

25:38.121 --> 25:40.206
<i>but the whole point</i>
<i>of trying to win</i>

25:40.248 --> 25:41.958
<i>a second straight</i>
<i>gold medal</i>

25:42.000 --> 25:44.085
<i>is that it isn't</i>
<i>supposed to be easy...</i>

25:44.127 --> 25:46.046
<i>just the way they like it.</i>

25:46.087 --> 25:48.715
You are something.

25:48.757 --> 25:50.050
<i>It's the Olympic trials.</i>

25:50.091 --> 25:52.052
<i>I love playing</i>
<i>on a big stage</i>

25:52.093 --> 25:53.887
<i>and hopefully prove</i>
<i>that we're</i>

25:53.928 --> 25:56.681
still a top team
would be just...

25:56.723 --> 25:58.808
the bees' knees.

25:58.850 --> 26:00.393
We can edit that out in post.

26:00.435 --> 26:02.228
<i>- We have a lot of confidence</i>
<i>in our abilities,</i>

26:02.270 --> 26:04.064
<i>and we know that</i>
<i>if we come and play</i>

26:04.105 --> 26:05.732
<i>how we're capable of playing,</i>

26:05.774 --> 26:07.108
we have a great chance
at winning.

26:07.150 --> 26:08.234
Close!

26:08.276 --> 26:10.111
<i>To not really have</i>
<i>that pressure</i>

26:10.153 --> 26:11.863
of having to like go back
and wanting to repeat--

26:11.905 --> 26:13.573
my pressure is just
in wanting to get there.

26:13.615 --> 26:16.868
<i>It's just all business.</i>

26:16.910 --> 26:19.120
- Yep--switch switching goal!
Yep!

26:19.162 --> 26:21.081
<i>- So they might seem like</i>
<i>the favorites</i>

26:21.122 --> 26:22.874
<i>heading into trials,</i>

26:22.916 --> 26:27.128
<i>but time will tell if, when</i>
<i>you mix grit with grins...</i>

26:27.170 --> 26:29.047
- Okay, yep.
<i>- Balanced veterans</i>

26:29.089 --> 26:32.425
<i>with some new blood</i>
<i>and then add ice,</i>

26:32.467 --> 26:36.429
<i>you get the recipe</i>
<i>for another shot at gold.</i>

26:36.471 --> 26:37.931
<i>- I think the trials</i>
<i>are way more pressure</i>

26:37.972 --> 26:39.140
<i>than the Olympics.</i>

26:39.182 --> 26:41.893
There's so much...
so much on the line.

26:41.935 --> 26:43.645
That was pure, Shu.

26:43.687 --> 26:45.522
That's gold!

26:45.563 --> 26:47.774
Man, it makes me nervous

26:47.816 --> 26:50.235
just thinking about it.

26:51.695 --> 26:54.030
<i>- Next time,</i>
<i>on "American Rock Stars,"</i>

26:54.072 --> 26:55.407
<i>the trials.</i>

26:55.448 --> 26:57.575
<i>- For the nation's</i>
<i>top curlers,</i>

26:57.617 --> 26:59.869
<i>the road to Beijing</i>
<i>goes through Omaha.</i>

26:59.911 --> 27:02.622
<i>- Team Shuster starts</i>
<i>their ten-day trials journey</i>

27:02.664 --> 27:03.915
<i>as the team to beat.</i>

27:03.957 --> 27:05.500
Hard!

27:05.542 --> 27:06.668
Attaboy, Matty.

27:06.710 --> 27:08.962
<i>- But a collection</i>
<i>of upstart rivals</i>

27:09.004 --> 27:10.588
<i>calling themselves</i>
<i>The Young Bucks</i>

27:10.630 --> 27:12.632
<i>look to crash the ice party,</i>

27:12.674 --> 27:15.051
<i>hoping they can be the team</i>

27:15.093 --> 27:17.512
<i>that represents the U.S.</i>
<i>at the Olympics.</i>
